Synopsis:
   save [<options>] [<filename>]

Description:
   SAVE is used to record the client's current configuration to an
   external file; if none is specified, the ~/.BitchX/BitchX.sav is used, 
   or the name of the file specified on the command line. The
   command does not save some information.

Examples:
   To save everything:
      /save 

See Also:
   Command_Line_Args(7); load(5); stub(5)
